obj": "cell_line", "prob": 0.6866793632507324, "span": {"begin": 1190, "end": 1195}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "hESC", "obj": "species", "prob": 0.7718629837036133, "span": {"begin": 1190, "end": 1194}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "fetal-, neonatal- and adult-derived CD34+ HSPCs", "obj": "cell_type", "prob": 0.9023170471191406, "span": {"begin": 1197, "end": 1244}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "hESC", "obj": "species", "prob": 0.842084527015686, "span": {"begin": 1266, "end": 1270}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "CD34+ HSPCs", "obj": "cell_type", "prob": 0.7680487632751465, "span": {"begin": 1306, "end": 1317}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:947"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "CD34+", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.98237544298172, "span": {"begin": 1306, "end": 1311}}, {"id": ["mim:601308"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "MLL", "obj": "disease", "prob": 0.9999703168869019, "span": {"begin": 1377, "end": 1380}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:3014"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "&gamma;-H2AX", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.8576852083206177, "span": {"begin": 1441, "end": 1453}}, {"id": ["mesh:D005047"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "etoposide", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9378750920295715, "span": {"begin": 1539, "end": 1548}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:3014"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "&gamma;-H2AX", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9211112260818481, "span": {"begin": 1594, "end": 1606}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "Peripheral Blood -derived CD34+ HSPCs", "obj": "cell_type", "prob": 0.8517246842384338, "span": {"begin": 1681, "end": 1718}}, {"id": ["mesh:D005047"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "etoposide", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9969913959503174, "span": {"begin": 1794, "end": 1803}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "hESC", "obj": "cell_line", "prob": 0.5837544202804565, "span": {"begin": 1838, "end": 1842}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:4297"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "MLL", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9826322793960571, "span": {"begin": 1873, "end": 1876}}, {"id": ["mesh:D005047"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "etoposide", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9879598617553711, "span": {"begin": 1941, "end": 1950}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "undifferentiated hESC", "obj": "cell_line", "prob": 0.9048953652381897, "span": {"begin": 1961, "end": 1982}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "hESC", "obj": "species", "prob": 0.7005228400230408, "span": {"begin": 1978, "end": 1982}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "HESC-derived CD34", "obj": "cell_line", "prob": 0.7167800664901733, "span": {"begin": 1987, "end": 2004}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "HESC-derived CD34+ hematopoietic cells", "obj": "cell_type", "prob": 0.7805088758468628, "span": {"begin": 1987, "end": 2025}}], "text": "&nbsp;  Etoposide treatment in vivo in mice at day 13.5 of pregnancy induces MLL breakage in fetal liver haematopoietic stem cells in utero, but MLL-rearranged fusion mRNAs were detected only in mice which were defective in the DNA damage response, i.e. atm knockout mice. A fusion gene analogous to MLL-AF4 was not detectable in the wild type mice. In this study, an intraperitoneal injection of 10 mg/kg of etoposide into pregnant mice at day 13.5 of pregnancy resulted in a maximum fetal liver concentration of about 5 &micro;M. A dose of 0.5 mg/kg did not result in a measurable concentration. A statistically significant increase (about 6-fold) in DSBs in the MLL gene of isolated fetal liver haematopoietic stem cells was observed after a single dose of 1 mg/kg to pregnant mice. A clear activation of DNA damage response was observed at the dose of 10 mg/kg (Nanya et al. 2016).  There is&nbsp;information about etoposide-induced DSB&nbsp;and MLL chromosomal translocation in human HSPCs at different ontogeny stages, spanning from embryonic to adult HSPCs.&nbsp;  In vitro, a single-pulse of etoposide&nbsp;induced DSBs measured by g-H2AX staining in all primary cell types tested (hESC-, fetal-, neonatal- and adult-derived CD34+ HSPCs) &nbsp;In embryonic (hESC-derived) and neonatal (CB-derived) CD34+ HSPCs ETO showed a significant trend towards higher frequency of MLL breaks than control. Median fluorescence intensity (MFI) of &gamma;-H2AX determined at 3h, 6h, and 12h after a single-pulse (0 h) exposure&nbsp;to 10&micro;M etoposide&nbsp;rapidly (3 h) induced the expression of &gamma;-H2AX regardless the cell type targeted. Fetal Bone Marrow, Cord Blood&nbsp;and Peripheral Blood -derived CD34+ HSPCs managed to partially repair the DSBs overtime (6 h and 12 h). In contrast, etoposide-induced DSBs seem irreversible in hESC (Rodriguez et al. 2020).&nbsp;MLL&nbsp;gene breaks was demonstrated upon single-pulse exposure to etoposide at 1uM in undifferentiated hESC and HESC-derived CD34+ hematopoietic cells&nbsp;(Rodriguez et al. 2020)", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 15:00:05 +0000 2026"}